<subSubSection pageId="73" pageNumber="74" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="73.[151,1437,1022,1155]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[151,261,1022,1047]" class="Insecta" family="Corixidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Corixidae</taxonomicName>
is one of the richest families of aquatic bugs in 
<collectingCountry box="[857,971,1022,1047]" name="Argentina" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, with 28 recorded species in 5 genera. Following 
<bibRefCitation author="Hungerford" box="[282,504,1058,1083]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" refString="Hungerford, H. B. (1948) The Corixidae of the Western Hemisphere (Hemiptera). University of Kansas Science Bulletin, 32, 1 - 827, pls. i - cxii." type="journal article" year="1948">Hungerford (1948)</bibRefCitation>
, six subfamilies are currently recognized, of which only the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="WE.Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[1270,1380,1058,1083]" class="Insecta" family="Corixidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Corixinae">Corixinae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hungerford" authorityYear="1948" box="[151,332,1094,1119]" class="Insecta" family="Corixidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Heterocorixinae">Heterocorixinae</taxonomicName>
are represented in the Argentinean fauna; the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jaczewski" authorityYear="1924" box="[855,1017,1094,1119]" class="Insecta" family="Corixidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Micronectinae">Micronectinae</taxonomicName>
are here treated as a separate family. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hungerford" box="[151,362,1130,1155]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" refString="Hungerford, H. B. (1948) The Corixidae of the Western Hemisphere (Hemiptera). University of Kansas Science Bulletin, 32, 1 - 827, pls. i - cxii." type="journal article" year="1948">Hungerford (1948)</bibRefCitation>
subdivided the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="WE.Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[540,650,1130,1155]" class="Insecta" family="Corixidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Corixinae">Corixinae</taxonomicName>
in four tribes, out of which only 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[1018,1109,1130,1155]" class="Insecta" family="Corixidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Corixini">Corixini</taxonomicName>
is represented in the country.
</paragraph>
